SECTION 4 — Operational Signatures 

Diagnostic Decision Tree (per phase)
Each phase is tested by a binary-branch sequence. Answer sequentially; first “No” flags the current phase.
Constraint Resolution Check
Has the prior phase’s defining constraint reached zero valid states?
→ Yes → proceed
→ No → still prior phase (or oscillation failure)
New Form Appearance Check
Has a new coherent form (bounded, recurrent under current load) appeared?
→ Yes → proceed
→ No → Integration stall or collapse
Bounded Recurrence Check (critical guardrail for Emergence vs. Premature Transition)
Does the new form persist across ≥3 constraint cycles without external support and remain stable under modest load increase?
→ Yes → true Emergence / Formalization entry
→ No → Premature Transition (form appeared before prior constraint resolved; destabilizes rapidly)
Linkage & Activation Check
Are isolated structures now linked (Bridging) and do linkages sustain activation without external drive (Ignition)?
→ Yes → proceed
→ No → fragmentation
Field Coherence Check
Does the system now operate as a single coherent field under accumulated constraints (Synthesis)?
→ Yes → Synthesis basin
→ No → return to Bridging/Ignition
Transition Triggers (observable sequence)
constraint mismatch (no valid state)
→ instability (increased oscillation amplitude)
→ phase shift (new constrained region of state-space)

